The paper deals with scheduling tasks on computational resources, which is a common problem in computer science. The use of anytime algorithms and quality control heuristics suggests a focus on artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and machine learning (cs.LG). The use of heterogeneous resources and the need for efficient scheduling suggests a focus on distributed computing (cs.DC) and systems and control (cs.SY). Finally, the proposal of a general procedure for estimating the relationship between processing time and quality suggests a focus on programming languages (cs.PL).
